name: Selenium 3.5.3
body:
• Fix wrapping of maps with null values. Fixes #3380 :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Unused imports :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Unused import :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Linking ignored tests to the corresponding issue :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Fixing encoding of payload passed by hub to a node :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Move `ActiveSession` and `Session` even closer :: Simon Stewart
  • Implement screenshot saving for InMemorySession :: Simon Stewart
  • Remove unused field :: Simon Stewart
  • [py] convert OSS capabilities to W3C equivalent for W3C payload :: lmtierney
  • [py] add IE Options class :: lmtierney
  • [py] allow IE WebDriver to accept IE Options :: lmtierney
  • Add temporary iOS platform to aid W3C migration (#4559) :: Luke Inman-Semerau
  • remove unnecessary pytest marking, address flake8 issues :: Lucas Tierney
  • Make Chrome driver aware of touch actions :: Alex Rodionov
  • Fix incorrect documentation for Chrome emulation :: Alex Rodionov
  • Allow passing speed to flick action :: Alex Rodionov
  • Don't print mouse/key deprecations on using TouchActionBuilder :: Alex Rodionov
  • Ignore difference in browser handling of links with the same blank target :: Alex Rodionov
  • Synchronizing "platform" and "platformName" capability values. Fixes #4565 :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Defending against chromedriver that sometimes returns null value as the result of findElements operation. See #4555 :: Alexei Barantsev
  • No logical change: minor java 8 syntax tweak :: Simon Stewart
  • Prevent a Grid Hub blindly assuming 404 == dead session :: Simon Stewart
  • [Grid]: Handle poorly formed JSON responses :: Simon Stewart
  • Unignored marionette tests fixed in nightly :: Alexei Barantsev
  • [Grid]: Add a w3c status endpoint for nodes and hubs :: Simon Stewart
  • Add a target for running Grid tests :: Simon Stewart
  • Forgot to wire the GridSupplier into the WebDriverBuilder :: Simon Stewart
  • Add shortcut targets for running grid tests :: Simon Stewart
  • Grid tests are also remote tests :: Simon Stewart
  • Actions: correctly fill sequences :: Simon Stewart
  • Fixing javadoc to match OSS spec :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Linking ignored tests to bug reports :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Adding a new test inspired by issue #578. Driver should be able to set page load timeout once and handle sequential pages with load timeouts. :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Ensure DriverService instances found by ServiceLocators are used :: Simon Stewart
  • ActiveSession: allow new factories to be bound :: Simon Stewart
  • Add new test into test suite :: Simon Stewart
  • Adding tests for focus and blur events inspired by #825 :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Ignoring just added tests in marionette :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Ignoring recently added test in legacy Firefox driver :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Fixing a grid test: two new status servlets were added recently :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Oops, there are two checks in this test, only one was fixed in the previous commit :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Linking ignored test to bug report :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Return toReturn. :: GitHub
  • Adding tests for executeScript that returns recursive structures :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Grid tests need geckodriver apparently :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Ignoring failed tests :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Adding a test for click to an element partially (>50%) hidden by overflow :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Implementing ability to ignore tests in grid environment :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Bump Java version number to 3.5.3 :: Simon Stewart
  • All Platforms have a family. :: Simon Stewart
  • Avoid throwing an exception in RemoteWebDriver.toString() :: Simon Stewart
  • A Platform family returns `null` from `getFamily` :: Simon Stewart
  • Update java release targets :: Simon Stewart
  • Update java changelog one last time :: Simon Stewart

name: Selenium 3.5.2
body:
• Handle stacktrace from legacy Firefox driver :: Alex Rodionov
  • Deprecate Alert#authenticate :: Alex Rodionov
  • Updating Java CHANGELOG for version 3.5. Fixes #3877 :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Unignoring a bunch of tests in marionette, file uploading and d-n-d work now :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Ensure we append text to the end of content editables. :: Simon Stewart
  • Move the content editable test into ContentEditableTest :: Simon Stewart
  • Mark content editable tests as not yet implemented :: Simon Stewart
  • Safari returns "macOS" as the platform :: Simon Stewart
  • This test requires a fresh browser in marionette too :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Ignore rules should recognize Edge :: Alexei Barantsev
  • A temporarily solution: official littleproxy release is not compatible with guava 22. We use littleproxy just to run ProxySettingTest in Java, so it's safe enough to use a custom build that fixes guava incompatibility. :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Updating IE driver atoms to properly return element position :: Jim Evans
  • Updating IE driver prebuilts for 3.5.1 point-release :: Jim Evans
  • Implementing /wd/hub/sessions endpoint in selenium server :: Alexei Barantsev
  • Add the `/file` endpoint to the new server :: Simon Stewart
  • Creating temp dir for files uploaded to remote server. :: Alexei Barantsev
  • [py] Add Safari to API docs [skip ci] :: Dave Hunt
  • Remove unused import. :: GitHub
  • [js] Add a new ElementNotInteractableError :: Jason Leyba
  • [js] Update examples & docs to not rely on btnG on the Google search page :: Jason Leyba
  • Migrate from GSON to our own serializer/deserializer :: Simon Stewart
  • More migration to our own JSON serialisers :: Simon Stewart
  • InMemorySession does not need a second tempfs :: Simon Stewart
  • Move Session and ActiveSession closer :: Simon Stewart
  • Attempt to avoid sending doubles instead of longs in JSON :: Simon Stewart
  • Bump Java version to 3.5.2 :: Simon Stewart
  • Correct the CHANGELOG :: Simon Stewart
  • More CHANGELOG shenanigans :: Simon Stewart
  • Once more updating version numbers :: Simon Stewart

name: Selenium 3.5.1
body:

  • Updating .NET projects to use Visual Studio 2017 :: Jim Evans

  • Updating .editorconfig to work with Visual Studio 2017 :: Jim Evans
  • Updating C++ projects to work with Visual Studio 2017 :: Jim Evans
  • Bumping version resources and CHANGELOG for .NET 3.5.1 point-release :: Jim Evans

  • Bump java version to 3.5.1 :: Simon Stewart
  • Handle null values in stack traces when marshalling exceptions :: Simon Stewart
  • Allow non-local connections. :: GitHub
  • Initial support for .NET Core :: Jim Evans
  • Release selenium-webdriver 3.5.1 :: Alex Rodionov
  • Correctly process driver stacktrace upon error :: Alex Rodionov
  • Enable debug mode when DEBUG environment variable is set :: Alex Rodionov
  • Fix node Options documentation (#4479) :: Lucas Tierney
  • Updating .NET FirefoxOptions to not force specifying binary location :: Jim Evans
  • Accept negative default window position. :: GitHub

name: Selenium 3.0.1
body:
## Java
- Include ElementScrollBehavior enum in the release.
- Add dependency on HTMLUnit to be included in the standalone server.
- Grid new session requests pass original request through to the node
  without any modifications.
- Fix NPE in htmlrunner when port is not specified.
- FirefoxDriver (legacy) fix to cleanup temp filesystem on quit (#2914 #2908).

## Ruby
- Implement #driver_path as parameter when initializing a driver (thanks lmtierney)
- Improve Ruby syntax in driver commands (thanks joe_schulte)
- Improve performance when shutting down drivers (thanks lmtierney)
- Fix bug for finding open ports on Windows (thanks kou1okada)
- Fix bug in auto detection of drivers which allowed selection of non-executable binaries

#### W3C
- Implement #cookie_named and #delete_all_cookies methods (thanks lmtierney)
- Implement element #property method (thanks lmtierney)

#### Chrome
- Fix bug in switches (thanks danvine)

## Python
- Fix regressions with python 3
- Add support for Safari Technology Preview

name: Selenium 3.0.0
body:
IMPORTANT CHANGES
- Firefox is only fully supported at version 47.0.1 or earlier. Support
  for later versions of firefox is provided by geckodriver, which is
  based on the evolving W3C WebDriver spec, and uses the wire protocol
  in that spec, which is liable to change without notice.
- You may wish to choose an ESR release such as 45.4.0esr or earlier.
- Firefox 47.0.0 is not supported at all.

Other major changes:
- Stability fixes in Grid.
- All Grid nodes can now offer help.
- Updated to the latest version of HtmlUnitDriver.
- Re-enabled log gathering for the standalone server.
- Firefox profile is passed to both the legacy FirefoxDriver and
  geckodriver.
